sources.description: Calculated using 2025 IRS tax tables and FICA rates
sources.notes: Taxable income: $200,000 - $31,500 = $168,500. Tax calculated through 22% bracket. SS: $200,000 * 6.2% = $12,400 (under wage base). Medicare: $200,000 * 1.45% = $2,900. No additional Medicare (under $250k for married joint)
